The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Kerala patch-up

 Thiruvananthapuram, March 24: Three days after ruling out a return to the Congress, K. Karunakaran today reached an electoral adjustment with the coalition headed by the party, reports our special correspondent.

 Democratic Indira Congress (K) president K. Muraleedharan signed an agreement with state Congress chief Ramesh Chennithala. 

 No one can drive a wedge between Sonia (Gandhi) and me, Karunakaran said.

 His party will contest from only 18 seats, including one loaned by the Congress, according to the pact that was signed in the presence of chief minister Oommen Chandy.

 Politburo candidate

 The CPM politburo did a turnaround today, deciding to field V.S. Achuthanandan in the Assembly elections.

 CPM general secretary Prakash Karat made the announcement this evening . 

 The politburo had earlier decided to keep members out of the poll fray.




